body.description: Introducing the Lane Linen 450 Thread Count 100% Long Staple Cotton Sheet Set, the perfect blend of comfort and style for your bedroom. Made from premium quality long staple cotton, these sheets are soft, breathable, and durable, providing you with a luxurious sleeping experience every night. With nine sizes available, including Twin, Twin XL, Full, Queen, King, Calking, Split King, Standard & King Pillow pair, you can choose the perfect fit for your bed. The Lane Linen Sheet Set also comes in 10 solid colors and 4 print designs, so you can match your existing décor or add a pop of color to your room. These sheets are expertly crafted with a 450 thread count, ensuring a silky smooth finish that feels great against your skin. The fitted sheet features deep pockets to fit mattresses up to 16 inches deep, providing a secure fit that won't slip or bunch up during the night. In addition to being comfortable and stylish, the Lane Linen Sheet Set is also easy to care for. Simply machine wash and tumble dry for a quick and hassle-free cleaning process. Invest in the Lane Linen 450 Thread Count 100% Long Staple Cotton Sheet Set and enjoy a good night's sleep in style and comfort.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2024
reviews.reviewText: First off, some of the reviews I have read on the negative side, are nothing at all what I experienced. They are thick and silky smooth at first feel. I bought these on sale and in all fairness, had I not known the feel of 800 or 1000 thread count sateen sheets, I might not have been bothered by this purchase, but alas I do. I paid the same for these, as my 800 and have to say they are not nearly as soft after washing. I did not try sleeping on them, because I wanted to make sure I returned them unused. You might ask why I would buy this low of a thread count when I I paid the same for 800? Honestly, after reading so much on thread count and cotton, etc. my head was ready to explode. I wanted to see if there was that big of a difference and if all the hoopla was warranted. Well, yes, it is. I washed both sets of sheets at the same time, almost the exact same color, and upon pulling them out of the dryer, and immediately touching the sheets, could feel that there was a huge difference in the fabric. I wasn't yet sure which was which, so I separated them. I then went back on line to match the brand to the sheet sets and confirm which was the 450 and the 800. It was the 800 that was super soft. I couldn't justify spending the exact same price on such a huge quality difference. I bought both during the Christmas sales, so that is probably why I got such a good deal on the 800 count. I honestly don't know if they are bad for the price. I keep my sheets for a long time and have no idea what is realistic these days for 450 sateen. All I know, is that I was comparing apples to apples price wise, and they were night and day different. What it boils down to, is if you can get 800 sateen for anything close to what you pay for a 450 sateen, you should get it because there is definitely a difference. I do not know how they fit, because they did not make it that far!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I wanted 100% cotton sheets, and found these and thought the price was good and figured what they hey lets give them a try. I just got them home, washed them and put them on the bed. The fitted sheet fit perfectly, even with a bit of room for shrinkage if that happens with future washings. The elastic seems like a good quality so I expect these sheets to last for quite some time. The flat sheet was again plenty big enough and hopefully it will not shrink over time either. The color (I went with Estate Blue) is gorgeous. The quality of these sheets is what I was hoping for but wasn't holding my breathe. I am very happy and plan to buy another set, this time I will go with black because I have always wanted black sheets. Anyways, I do wish there was more darker or patterns to choose from. I do not do white sheets and am tired of light colored sheets, there is just no drama to them.
